# never import error classes manually in reducer code

```typescript
// ❌ Don't manually import error classes
import { MissingIdError } from "../../gen/module-name/error.js";
throw new MissingIdError("message");

// ❌ Don't use nested access patterns
throw new errors.ModuleName.MissingIdError("message");

// ✅ Just reference the error by name — auto-imported
throw new MissingIdError("message");
```

Since [[error classes in reducers are auto-imported by name reference]], the code generator scans for error class names and inserts the correct imports. Manual imports conflict with auto-generated ones, creating duplicate import errors or path mismatches.

